===Etymology===
From late {{inh|en|enm|sausige}}, from {{der|en|xno|saussiche}} (compare {{cog|nrf|saûciche}}), from {{der|en|LL.|salsīcia}} (compare {{cog|scn|sausizza}}, {{cog|es|salchicha}}, {{cog|it|salsiccia}}), feminine of {{m|la|salsīcius||seasoned with salt}}, derivative of {{der|en|la|salsus||salted}}, from {{m|la|sal||salt}}. More at {{l|en|salt}}. {{doublet|en|saucisse}}. See also {{cog|scn|sausizza}}.

